Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Make sure you are balancing your running with resistance training and core strength too. Continuing with some neck physio and an emphasis on ergonomics at your desk will go a long way to reduce the paraesthesia (tingling) that you are experiencing at night in your hands. (position and no red flags)
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: We are going to repeat your hormones after you have been off of the pill for three months and can consider hormone replacement or DHEA at that time.

Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologist for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram annually.
Overview Notes: Find healthy ways to destress and calm your mind. Take a stab at some mindfulness exercises and see if you can find the right fit. Practice makes perfect.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamNote
Comment Value: In excellent health on the day of the medical.
Special Investigation Notes: We are going to repeat your hormones after you have been off of the pill for three months and can consider hormone replacement or DHEA at that time.

Overview Notes: We will review your hormone and adrenal profile with repeat bloods after being off of the pill for three months. At the same time, we can repeat your thyroid function profile and ALT.

Continuing with some neck physio and an emphasis on ergonomics at your desk will go a long way to reduce the paraesthesia (tingling) that you are experiencing at night in your hands. (position and no red flags)
Comment Key: CurrentComplaintRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: We are going to repeat your hormones after you have been off of the pill for three months and can consider hormone replacement or DHEA at that time.

Continuing with some neck physio and an emphasis on ergonomics at your desk will go a long way to reduce the paraesthesia (tingling) that you are experiencing at night in your hands. (position and no red flags)
Comment Key: LabTestNote
Comment Value: Your TSH is suppressed due to your thyroid treatment. Your adrenal profile suggests stress which you are aware of. Your liver enzymes are minutely elevated; for review.
Special Investigation Notes: We are going to repeat your hormones after you have been off of the pill for three months and can consider hormone replacement or DHEA at that time.

Overview Notes: We will review your hormone and adrenal profile with repeat bloods after being off of the pill for three months. At the same time, we can repeat your thyroid function profile and ALT.

Continuing with some neck physio and an emphasis on ergonomics at your desk will go a long way to reduce the paraesthesia (tingling) that you are experiencing at night in your hands. (position and no red flags)
Comment Key: LifestyleRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: We are going to repeat your hormones after you have been off of the pill for three months and can consider hormone replacement or DHEA at that time.

Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologist for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram annually.
Overview Notes: Your blood pressure was slightly elevated on the day of your medical. Please keep an eye on this and pop by for some random checks in case we need to intervene. Reducing stress and reducing salt and coffee will also help to keep it in check.
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryRecommendation
Comment Value: Keep choosing a healthy lifestyle to reduce your risk for developing familial related chronic illnesses.
Special Investigation Notes: We are going to repeat your hormones after you have been off of the pill for three months and can consider hormone replacement or DHEA at that time.

Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologist for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram annually.
Overview Notes: We will review your hormone and adrenal profile with repeat bloods after being off of the pill for three months. At the same time, we can repeat your thyroid function profile and ALT.
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryRecommendation
Comment Value: Keep choosing a healthy lifestyle to reduce your risk for developing familial related chronic illnesses.
Special Investigation Notes: We are going to repeat your hormones after you have been off of the pill for three months and can consider hormone replacement or DHEA at that time.

Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologist for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram annually.
Overview Notes: We will review your hormone and adrenal profile with repeat bloods after being off of the pill for three months. At the same time, we can repeat your thyroid function profile and ALT.
Comment Key: MentalHealthStressRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: We are going to repeat your hormones after you have been off of the pill for three months and can consider hormone replacement or DHEA at that time.
